          "title": "About the Course",
          "entries": [
            {
              "title": "About the Course",
              "content": "Explore each region of Canada, its geological features, cultural geography, symbols, and varied ecosystems. Along the way, students practice their mapping skills by making models and drawing places local to them, such as their neighborhood."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "kind": "tips-group",
          "title": "Placement & Combining Tips",
          "entries": [
            {
              "title": "Placement & Combining Tips",
              "content": "This course progresses chronologically over two years, studying half of Canada's provinces and territories each year. This course is intended as a precursor to Grade 3; however, the levels may be reversed in order to combine students.\nStudents who did not take Geography Foundations may wish to incorporate those lessons into the afternoons."
            }
          ]
        },
